You must ensure that the slot invoke changes the object it lives on atomically. That is to say, between the O and the X you must have restored the state of the class to a point where any of it's slots can be called. Queues work best, and Qt uses queues internally for you via signals/slots. If all your slots for a given object ensure that between O and X the state of the object is restored, all proper invocations of all slots for that object are guaranteed to be thread safe.
